équy, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, França":"Créquy, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Nevers","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["French: habitational name from the city of Nevers in France.","Possibly an altered form of English   Nevard   or perhaps of its extinct variant <b>Neverd</b>. The surname <i>Nevers</i> is also found in Jamaica.","History: The majority of the American bearers of this surname trace their origin to Richard Nevers, born in 1666 in Woburn, MA. His origin is not known, but his surname is also documented in the forms <i>Nevard</i> and <i>Neverds</i>, which make it possible that Richard Nevers was of English origin."],"variants":[{"name":"Nevard","meanings":["(2010: NA)","English: from the Middle English (Old French) personal name <i>Nevard</i>, from ancient Germanic <i>Niwhard</i>, from <i>niw-</i> ‘new’ + <i>hard-</i> ‘strong, hardy’. Compare   Nevers  ."]}]},{"name":"dite","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English:  See  Dyte  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dyte","meanings":["English: nickname, perhaps from an unrecorded Middle English * <i>dight</i>, a side-form of Middle English  <i>dought</i> ‘brave, valiant’, and possibly derived therefore from a shortened form of Old English  <i>dyhtig</i>,  <i>dohtig</i> ‘doughty’.  Compare  Doughty  ."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of any of the given names beginning with the letter <i>D-</i> (  compare  Jay   and   Kay  ), in particular   Dorothy .  It is also used as an independent name, and may in some cases be associated with the River Dee (  compare  Clyde  )."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Poméranie","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Americanized form of Jewish (Ashkenazic) and possibly also German   Pomeranz  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Pomeranz","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Kuna, Shlomo.","Jewish (Ashkenazic): artificial name from Yiddish <i>pomerants</i> ‘orange’ (German <i>Pomeranze</i>; see 2 below).","German: variant of <b>Pommeranz</b>, metonymic occupational name for an importer or seller of bitter (Seville) oranges, Middle High German <i>pomeranz</i> (from medieval Latin <i>pomarancia</i>, composed of the elements Latin <i>pomum</i> ‘apple, fruit’ and <i>arancia</i>, the name imported with the fruit; see   Naranjo  ). This form of the surname is very rare in Germany."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Mahaut dite de Poméranie Nevers was born in 1119, in Craon, Mayenne, Pays de la Loire, France. She married Raoul III de Créquy in 1140, in Reclinghem, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in 1160, in Créquy, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France, at the age of 41."},"et":{"1119–1160":"1119–1160","1120–1181":"1120–1181","1140–1226":"1140–1226","1149–1190":"1149–1190","1190":"1190","1149":"1149","1226":"1226","aproximadamente 1140":"umbes 1140","1120":"1120","1140":"1140","1160":"1160","1181":"1181","1119":"1119","Reclinghem, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France":"Reclinghem, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Créquy, Pas-Calés, Heuts-d'Franche, Française":"Créquy, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa","Créquy, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, França":"Créquy, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Craon, Mayenne, Pays de la Loire, França":"Craon, Mayenne, Pays de la Loire, Prantsusmaa","Créquy, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, França":"Créquy, Pas-de-Calais, Nord-Pas-de-Calais, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1119–1160":"1119–1160","1120–1181":"1120–1181","1140–1226":"1140–1226","1149–1190":"1149–1190","1190":"1190","1149":"1149","1226":"1226","aproximadamente 1140":"noin 1140